      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPICE IS RIGHT (1) resumes in a similar race to his last run nine months ago when ninth. Capable of playing a major role. LOVA SESSION (5) doesn't win out of turn, scoring just three times from 42 starts. Again tasted defeat last start when ninth over 1300m at Northam, beaten 3.5 lengths. Finds the right race this time and can salute. BIG SHOTS (3) has not appeared since he finished eighth over 1400m at Pinjarra Scarpside on January 25. Among the better hopes. KINGS CALL (7) comes here off a break of eight months. Worth noting he filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last time in work over 1300m at this track. Hasn't scored when fresh from a break but generally races well with two minor placings. Definite top-three chance.",
